[h4 id=NewTasRoute 
	"New TAS Route
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"In my previous TAS i would unlock the sled with the seemingly best performance from the beginning, then go into Quick Races to play through all the Open Mountain Tracks.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"The new TAS plays through the first Series (Pine Valley - Eagle Ridge) of the Open Mountain Championship in order to get a maxed out 800cc which has the best possible stats. After finishing Eagle Ridge the game will ask
	$LF
	"if you want to "Continue", "Save" or "Exit". I choose "Exit" here so i can go back to the menu and go to Quick Races and play through Glacial Grind - Lost Peak. 
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Exiting the championship after a Series ends lets you keep the purchased upgrades. Choosing to "Continue" will have you start another Series called "the foggies" where you have to play through Pine Valley - Eagle Ridge again, but in a dense fog. Obviously im not repeating the same tracks again.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=NewTasSled800ccVsOldTasSledCheatStormSledWhatIsTheDifference 
	"New TAS Sled (800cc) vs old TAS Sled (Cheat Storm Sled), what is the difference?
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"You will notice this immediately when you compare this TAS to the previous TAS. The 800cc is much more stable for movement in general, no stuns required to get into submarines and faster wallriding. Faster acceleration plays a key part of this sled
	$LF
	"aswell. I can now go for jumps i could not go for in the previous tas, because the Cheat Storm Sled was just terrible to use because of its poor acceleration. Backwards wallrides are also an option now because of the "Power Reverse" upgrade obtained in the Championship.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Because the 800cc is so much better in basically every regard, i spent a lot of time optimizing the movement to make it as perfect as possible.
	$LF
